What you need to know:

The Vet Lab Sports Club golfer made history by becoming the first golfer with an hearing impairment to clinch the Kenya Amateur Match Play Championship.The 29-year-old Makokha, a brother of Muthaiga based pro Jeff Kubwa and Eldoret based Reuben Kubwa, was four-up at the end of the first 18 holes in the match that attracted a number of golf enthusiasts.